Manager- E-Learning(Banking Industry)
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 07:15:35
Ref. JB3047354
Job Description
Main Role
Responsible for setting up and maintaining E-Learning, customer service and selling skills programs.
Principal Account abilities
•	Develop and implements strategy for the delivery of e Learning elements.
•	Conduct skill surveys to identify the skill gaps among the staff on a pro-active basis to ensure that they are technically equipped to handle the computer hardware/ software effectively and efficiently
•	Design training programs to support bank’s L&D; initiatives, ., content for computer-based, I-Pad, Mobile learning
•	Research and analyzes current eLearning technologies and best practices.
•	Develop and implements learning and development assessment tools
•	Partner with IT to effectively create eLearning solutions.
•	Set up and maintain E-Learning infrastructure.
•	Prepare and maintain all material related to E-Learning on all programs on Products,
Skills
Proven track record in managing e-learning programs, workshops and demonstrations; experience developing instructor-led training materials and self-paced learning content
